Title: Object: Sainte Famille de Iesus Christ
Object: Sacra Christi Familia
Description: Holy Family with saints, with at centre the seated Virgin supporting the standing Christ Child, on the right Sts Francis, Antony and Mary Magdalene; on the left St Elizabeth and the infant Baptist, and St Joseph; after a painting formerly attributed to Palma Vecchio, now to Bonifazio Veronese. 1682 Etching and engraving
Curator's comments: After the painting in the Musée du Louvre, Paris.
Associated names: Representation of: St Antony of Egypt
Representation of: St Francis of Assisi
Representation of: St John the Baptist (Prodromos)
